hopobject.body: A pension scheme drugs that will become generic in 2014 The odds of an asteroid impact are much higher than we commonly believe. There is a 30% chance of a city destroying asteroid to hit Earth in the next 100 years. A majority of the asteroids which hit Earth come from the asteroid belt between Jupiter and Mars. Jupiter, like a huge vacuum cleaner has sucked in hundreds of asteroids with its gigantic gravitational force and protects the Earth from potential killers like the one which is believed to have wiped out the Dinosaurs in the Jurassic Era.
